497 A.2d 482 William Everett ELLWOOD, Jr. v. STATE of Maryland. No. 16,

Sept. Term, 1985.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Sept. 13, 1985. Jerome James LaCorte and John L. Kopolow, Asst.-Public Defenders, Baltimore (Alan H. Murrell, Public Defender, Baltimore, on brief), for appellant. *43Carmina Szunyog Hughes, Asst. Atty. Gen., Baltimore (Stephen H. Sachs, Atty. Gen., Baltimore, on brief), for appellee.

Argued before MURPHY, C.J., and SMITH, ELDRIDGE, COLE, RODOWSKY, COUCH and McAULIFFE, JJ.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

The petition for writ of certiorari in the above entitled case having been granted and heard, it is this 13th day of September, 1985

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that the writ of certiorari be, and it is hereby, dismissed with costs, petition having been improvidently granted.
